headlines.description: Joshua Langford scored 12 of his 17 points in the first half to help No. 3 Michigan State take a huge lead it was able to restore in the second half against No. 5 Notre Dame in an 81-63 victory Thursday night.

headlines.description: Texas A&M junior guards D.J. Hogg and Admon Gilder scored 17 points each and the ninth-ranked Aggies used a 16-0 start to defeat Texas-Rio Grande Valley 78-60 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 9 Texas A&M beats Texas-Rio Grande Valley 78-60

headlines.description: Jevon Carter scored 25 points and grabbed nine rebounds and No. 19 West Virginia used an early second-half run to beat NJIT 102-69 on Thursday night.

headlines.description: Djimon Henson scored a career-high 23 points with five rebounds, Lamontray Harris added 16 and grabbed 10 rebounds, and Morehead State beat NAIA Div. II Alice Lloyd 103-56 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morehead State beats Alice Lloyd 103-56 behind Henson

headlines.description: Tyson Carter scored a career-high 35 points as Mississippi State remained unbeaten and defeated North Dakota State 83-59 on Thursday night.

headlines.description: Dimitri Thompson scored 23 points, including the go-ahead basket in overtime, and Elon beat South Florida 79-78 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Elon beats South Florida 79-78 in OT behind Thompson

headlines.description: Joe Chealey scored 18 points, Grant Riller added 17 and Charleston cruised to a 69-60 victory over Western Carolina on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Chealey, Riller lead Charleston past Western Carolina 69-60

headlines.description: Jordan King had a career-high 17 points and Bryson Scott added 13 as Fort Wayne roared out to an early lead to take a dominating 99-63 win over NAIA's IU-Kokomo on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: King leads Fort Wayne to 99-63 win over NAIA IU-Kokomo

headlines.description: Joe Hugley scored a career-high 21 points and grabbed eight rebounds to guide Central Connecticut State to a 72-59 win over North Carolina A&T on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: CCSU tops NC A&T 72-59 for fourth straight win

headlines.description: Joel Hernandez scored a career-best 27 points, grabbed a season-high 10 rebounds, and made a free throw with a second left to give LIU Brooklyn a 79-78 victory over Hartford on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hernandez leads LIU Brooklyn over Hartford 79-78

headlines.description: Justin Wright-Foreman had 23 points and Rokas Gustys had his second-consecutive double-double to help Hofstra cruise to a 107-72 win over Division II Molloy on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wright-Foreman, Gustys help Hofstra beat D-II Molloy 107-72

headlines.description: Vasa Pusica scored 22 points, Devon Begley added 14 off the bench and Northeastern defeated Harvard 77-61 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pusica has 22, Northeastern turns back Harvard 77-61

headlines.description: Shane Whitfield and Marcus Burk each scored 20 points and Campbell beat Stetson 85-78 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Whitfield, Burk score 20 each; Campbell beats Stetson 85-78

headlines.description: Brailen Neely came off the bench to score 22 points and dish off 13 assists, both career highs, and Oakland held off Texas Southern 97-87 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Neely's career night leads Oakland past Texas Southern 97-87

headlines.description: Charles Williams and R.J. Cole combined for 43 points as Howard rolled over Division II Central Pennsylvania 81-64 to get the Bison their first win of the season on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williams, Cole combine for 43 points, Howard gets 1st win

headlines.description: Alante Fenner had 17 points, on 6-of-8 shooting, and five steals and Zach Sellers scored 16 to help Savannah State beat Carver Bible College 98-60 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fenner, Sellers lead Savannah St. past Carver Bible College

headlines.description: Jamal Williams had a perfect night from the floor to total 14 points and lead Sam Houston State to a 77-54 victory over NAIA's St. Thomas (Texas) on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williams leads Sam Houston to 77-54 win over St. Thomas (TX)

headlines.description: Shawntrez Davis posted his fourth double-double of the season with 28 points and 10 rebounds and Bethune-Cookman beat Jacksonville 77-66 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Davis guides Bethune-Cookman past Jacksonville 77-66

headlines.description: B.J. Tyson scored nine of his career-high 30 points in overtime and Isaac Fleming finished with 21 points to help ECU beat UNC Wilmington 93-88 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tyson's 30 points help ECU beat UNC Wilmington 93-88 in OT

headlines.description: Chris Cokley had 18 points and 10 rebounds, and UAB snapped a 16-game losing streak against Memphis with a 71-56 victory on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: UAB snaps 16-game losing skid against Memphis, wins 71-56

headlines.description: Trae Young scored 21 of his 32 points in the second half to help Oklahoma defeat North Texas 82-72 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young's 32 points help Oklahoma beat North Texas 82-72

headlines.description: Matt Mooney scored 30 points on 10-of-14 shooting and made 8 of 9 free throws and South Dakota beat UMKC 82-63 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: S Dakota beats UMKC 82-63 behind Mooney's 30 points

headlines.description: Christian Cunningham and Cam Martin scored 12 points apiece and Jacksonville State shot 53.6 percent from the field in a 77-69 victory over Alabama State on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jacksonville St cruises past Alabama St 77-69

headlines.description: Quinton Rose scored a season-high 24 points to lead Temple to a 76-60 rout of South Carolina on Thursday night in the second game of the Under Armour Reunion at Madison Square Garden.
headlines.shortLinkText: Temple routs South Carolina 76-60 behind Rose's 24 points

headlines.description: Kassius Robertson and Jordan Barnett combined to make 14 of 23 from the field and scored 19 points apiece to help Missouri hold on for a 62-59 win over UCF on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barnett, Robertson scored 19 apiece as Missouri beats UCF

headlines.description: Jack Williams hit three 3-pointers and scored 13 points, and Anthony Townes and Jahlil Tripp added 11 points apiece as Pacific held off UC Riverside 57-55 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacific holds off UC Riverside 57-55

headlines.description: Franklin Porter and Josh McSwiggan had career nights as they combined for 39 points as Portland rolled over NAIA's Multnomah 112-65 to halt a three-game skid on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Portland halts 3-game skid, beats Multnomah 112-65

headlines.description: KJ Feagin hit four 3-pointers and scored all 16 of his points in the first half, and Santa Clara never trailed in beating Northern Arizona 89-57 on Thursday night for the Lumberjacks' first 0-7 start to a season since 1951-52.
headlines.shortLinkText: Santa Clara runs away from Northern Arizona, 89-57

headlines.description: A.J. Harris scored 18 points and New Mexico State rolled to an 80-60 victory over UTEP on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harris scores 18 points; New Mexico State beats UTEP 80-60

headlines.description: Jaron Hopkins had career highs of 29 points and seven steals and Deshon Taylor scored 18 to help Fresno State beat Weber State 83-71 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hopkins scores 29 to lead Fresno St. past Weber St., 83-71

headlines.description: Josh Hearlihy scored 13 points, grabbed a career-high 10 rebounds and tied his career best with seven assists to help Seattle beat Kennesaw State 66-54 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hearlihy's double-double helps Seattle beat Kennesaw State

headlines.description: Devin Watson scored 26 points and visiting San Diego State handed San Diego its first loss of the season, 66-57 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Watson leads San Diego State to 66-57 victory over Toreros

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
